FBIS3-23027 "jptot008__l94128" JPRS-TOT-94-008-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 1 March 1994 WEST EUROPE TURKEY PKK Bombs Istanbul Train Station, Kills Over 40 Cadets 40 Cadets Said Wounded TA1202113094 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 GMT 12 Feb 94 TA1202113094 Ankara TRT Television Network Language: Turkish Article Type:BFN [Announcer-read report over video] [Excerpt] A bomb exploded at the Tuzla train station in Istanbul this morning, killing four and injuring 40 Tuzla Infantry School non-commissioned officer cadets. According to a TRT correspondent, Tuzla Infantry School cadets arrived en masse at the Tuzla train station to leave on their weekend vacation. The students, who were waiting for the train to arrive from Gebze, sustained various injuries when one or two powerful bombs placed in a garbage bin exploded. Forty-four persons, most of whom are seriously injured, were taken to various hospitals. Four of the injured died in hospital. They have not been identified yet. [passage omitted]
